  • Classes in dto used by dto
    Class
    Description
    APXDeployedEntity
    The deployed entity is a SysML stereotype for a certain block type, it represents any of the sensors or microprocessors included in the environment.
    APXInterfaceDesignDescription
    The Interface Design Description (IDD) is a SysML stereotype that displays every service that a certain system provides including networking, format and security parameters.
    APXInterfaceDesignDescription.APXServiceDescription
    The ServiceDescriptizon is a SysML stereotype that displays the type and payload of an operation.
    APXInterfaceDesignDescription.APXServiceDescription.APXParameter
    The parameter of a certain ServiceDescription stereotype
    APXInterfaceDesignDescription.APXServiceDescription.APXPayload
    The payload of a certain ServiceDescription stereotype
    APXLocalCloudDesignDescription
    The Local Cloud Design Description is a SysML stereotype that includes a list of deployed entities with their associated System Design Descriptions
    APXLocalCloudDesignDescription.APXConnector
    The APXConnection is a data structure of the uml connection
    APXSystemDesignDescription
    The System Design Description is a SysML stereotype that describes the properties of a system regarding every interface that might work with
